he team\u2019s first season playing their home games at [[SoFi Stadium]] in [[Inglewood, California|Inglewood]], which the team will share with the [[2020 Los Angeles Chargers season|Los Angeles Chargers]]. They will look to improve on their [[2019 Los Angeles Rams season|9\u20137 season]] from the previous year and return to the playoffs after missing them last season.\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===Coaching changes===\n* On January 6, 2020, the Rams parted ways with long time defensive coordinator [[Wade Phillips]], whose contract was not renewed. Special teams coordinator [[John Fassel]], who had been with the franchise since 2012, was also not retained and took the same position with the [[Dallas Cowboys]]. Other staff members who did not return were assistant offensive coordinator [[Jedd Fisch]], running backs coach [[Skip Peete]], assistant special teams coach [[Matt Daniels]], and director of strength training and performance [[Ted Rath]].\n\n* Several staff members shifted responsibilities or added to their duties. Run game coordinator [[Aaron Kromer]] also became the team's offensive line coach, while pass game coordinator [[Shane Waldron]] retained that title but is no longer the quarterbacks coach.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/rams/story/2020-02-12/sean-mcvay-talks-about-newly-assembled-rams-coaching-staff|title=Sean McVay talks about newly assembled Rams coaching staff|website=LATimes.com|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref> Also, assistant wide receivers coach [[Zac Robinson]] and assistant quarterbacks coach [[Liam Coen]] swapped positions from the previous season.\n\n* [[Kevin O'Connell (American football)|Kevin O'Connell]] was hired as offensive coordinator and [[Brandon Staley]] took over as defensive coordinator. [[John Bonamego]] was brought on board as special teams coordinator and will be assisted by [[Tory Woodbury]]. [[Justin Lovett]] became the Rams' new director of strength training and performance.\n\n=== Uniform changes ===\n* In March 2019, the Rams announced they would debut new uniforms for the 2020 season.  The new logos and colors were revealed on March 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ramsnewlook.com/|title=Los Angeles Rams New Look|website=ramsnewlook.com|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>The new logos were heavily criticized.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/25/sports/football/rams-logo-angelo-state.html</ref> The new uniforms will be revealed sometime in May.\n\n==Roster changes==\n\n=== Free agency ===\n\n==== Unrestricted ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Position\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Player\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" |2020 team\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Date signed\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Contract\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|[[Defensive end|DE]]\n|[[Michael Brockers]]\n|[[Los Angeles Rams]]\n| March 27, 2020\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Linebacker|ILB]]\n|[[Cory Littleton]]\n|[[Las Vegas Raiders]]\n| March 25, 2020\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Linebacker|OLB]]\n| [[Dante Fowler]]\n| [[Atlanta Falcons]]\n| March 25, 2020\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Wide receiver|WR]]\n| [[Mike Thomas (wide receiver, born 1994)|Mike Thomas]]\n| [[Cincinnati Bengals]]\n| March 24, 2020\n|\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|[[Center (gridiron football)|C]]\n|[[Austin Blythe]]\n|[[Los Angeles Rams]]\n| March 26, 2020\n|\n|-\n|[[Quarterback|QB]]\n|[[Blake Bortles]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Placekicker|K]]\n|[[Greg Zuerlein (American football)|Greg Zuerlein]]\n|[[Dallas Cowboys]]\n| March 30, 2020\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Cornerback|CB]]\n|[[Nickell Robey-Coleman]]\n|[[Philadelphia Eagles]]\n| March 31, 2020\n|\n|-\n|[[Free Safety|FS]]\n|[[Marqui Christian]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-