Angeles Rams|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001066175/article/jaguars-trading-jalen-ramsey-to-los-angeles-rams|website=NFL.com|date=October 15, 2019|access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*The Rams traded their fifth-round selection, as well as a [[2019 NFL Draft|2019]] third-round selection to the [[2018 Jacksonville Jaguars season|Jaguars]] in exchange for [[linebacker]] [[Dante Fowler]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.therams.com/news/rams-acquire-edge-rusher-dante-fowler |title=Rams Acquire Edge Rusher Dante Fowler |last=Simmons |first=Myles |date=October 30, 2018 |website=TheRams.com |access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*The Rams traded cornerback [[Marcus Peters]] to the [[2019 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore Ravens]] in exchange for linebacker [[Kenny Young (American football)|Kenny Young]] and a fifth-round selection.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Owens |first1=Jason |title=Reports: Rams trade CB Marcus Peters to Ravens |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/reports-rams-trade-cb-marcus-peters-to-ravens-202408035.html |website=sports.yahoo.com |language=English |date=October 15, 2019 |access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref> The Rams later traded this selection as well as cornerback [[Aqib Talib]] to the [[2019 Miami Dolphins season|Miami Dolphins]] in exchange for a seventh-round selection in the [[2022 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rams ship CB Aqib Talib, fifth-rounder to Dolphins|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001071127/article/rams-ship-cb-aqib-talib-fifthrounder-to-dolphins|author=Patra, Kevin|website=NFL.com|date=October 29, 2019|access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*The Rams traded wide receiver [[Brandin Cooks]] and their fourth-round selection in [[2022 NFL Draft|2022]] to the [[2020 Houston Texans season|Houston Texans]] in exchange for the Texans' second-round pick (No. 57 overall).<ref>{{cite web|title=Rams agree to trade WR Brandin Cooks to Texans|url=https://www.therams.com/news/rams-agree-to-trade-wr-brandin-cooks-to-texans|author=Jackson, Stu|website=TheRams.com|date=April 10, 2020|access-date=April 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Staff==\n{{Los Angeles Rams staff}}\n\n==Current roster==\n{{Los Angeles Rams roster}}\n\n==Preseason==\nThe Rams' preseason opponents and schedule will be announced in the spring.\n\n==Regular season==\n<!--===Schedule===-->\n===2020 opponents===\nListed below are the Rams' opponents for [[2020 NFL season|2020]]. Exact dates and times will be announced in the spring.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Opponents Determined |url=https://nflcommunications.com/Pages/2020-Opponents-Determined.aspx |work=NFL Communications |date=December 30, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Category !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" width=200px| Home !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Los Angeles Rams|year=2020|border=2}}\" width=200px| Away\n|-\n| '''Division opponents'''<br>([[NFC West]]) || colspan=2| [[2020 Arizona Cardinals season|Arizona Cardinals]]<br>[[2020 San Francisco 49ers season|San Francisco 49ers]]<br>[[2020 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle Seahawks]]\n|-\n| '''Conference opponents'''<br>([[NFC East]]) || [[2020 Dallas Cowboys season|Dallas Cowboys]]<br>[[2020 New York Giants season|New York Giants]] || [[2020 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia Eagles]]<br>[[2020 Washington Redskins season|Washington Redskins]]\n|-\n| '''Conference opponents'''<br>(based on {{nfly|2019}} division placement) || [[2020 Chicago Bears season|Chicago Bears]] || [[2020 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n|-\n| '''Interconference opponents'''<br>([[AFC East]]) || [[2020 New England Patriots season|New England Patriots]]<br>[[2020 New York Jets season|New York Jets]] || [[2020 Buffalo Bills season|Buffalo Bills]]<br>[[2020 Miami Dolphins season|Miami Dolphins]]\n|}\n<!--\n===Game summaries===\n====Week #: vs. Arizona Cardinals====\n{{Americanf